headline: Will GoDaddy's (GDDY) Agent Name Service Launch Redefine Its Role in AI Identity Solutions?
summary: In the past week, GoDaddy launched public access to its Agent Name Service (ANS) API and standards site, offering developers tools to create, verify, and govern cryptographically secure identities for AI agents across protocols. This move highlights GoDaddy's focus on trusted identity solutions and interoperability as the agentic ecosystem evolves rapidly. The company's release of a protocol-agnostic identity system for AI agents stands out as a progressive step, enabling greater trust and...
